<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Google Fonts Blog</title>

  <!-- Import Google Fonts -->
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat&family=Oswald&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
      font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 36px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .container img {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .container p {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      text-align: justify;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Google Fonts</h1>

  <div class="container">
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/ee/Google_Fonts_logo.svg" alt="Google Fonts">
    
    <p>
      Google Fonts is a free and open-source library of web fonts developed by Google. It allows designers and developers
      to easily integrate high-quality typography into their websites. With a wide variety of font styles, weights, and
      languages, Google Fonts enhances both the readability and aesthetic of web content. Fonts like Oswald and Montserrat
      are widely used due to their versatility and professional appearance.
    </p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>





